- SO the diagram of images layers is like that
==================
= my-js-app:1.0  =   FROM node:13-alpine
==================
= node:13-alpine =   FROM alpine:3.10
==================
= alpine:3.10    =
==================


- Build docker image from dockerfile:
$ docker build -t (tag) my-app:1.0 .

- To Access container
$ docker exec -it 490d0b23b1b1 /bin/sh 



โ๏ธ ############# PRIVATE DOCKER REGISTRY ############


โ๏ธ ############# DOCER VOLUMES #######################

 ๐ข๏ธ For DATA PERSISTENCE : DB, Statefull applications, ...

When do we need Docker Volumes ?
- Data is GONE when Restarting or Removing the Container โ

What is Docker Volumes โ

________________________________
|            HOST ๐ฅ๏ธ           |
|   ________________________    |
|   |     CONTAINER๐ณ      |   |
|   |                       |   |
|   |  /var/lib/mysql/data ------------------> Virtual File System
|   |_______________________|   |
|                               |
|       /home/mount/data ๐------------------> HOST FILE SYSTEM (PHYSICAL โ๏ธ)
|_______________________________|

- Folder in PHYSICAL host file system ๐ฅ๏ธ is MOUNTED or PLUGED๐ into the virtual file system of container

- There is 3 types of volumes, but we will see just 2 : 

โ๏ธ 1 : HOST VOLUMES:
--------------------
$ docker run -v /home/mount/data:/var/lib/mysql/data
-> /home/mount/data : Host directory
-> /var/lib/mysql/data : Container Directory
โ you decide WHERE ON THE HOST FILE SYSTEM the reference is made


โ๏ธ 2 : NAMED  VOLUMES  ( โญ the used one in production envs ):
---------------------------------------------------------------
$ docker run -v name:/var/lib/mysql/data
-> /var/lib/mysql/data : Container Directory
โ you can REFERENCE the volume BY NAME
โ Should be used in production



โฌ๏ธ Define NAMED VOLUME in docker-compose file โฌ๏ธ :
โซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธโซ๏ธ
version: "3"
services:
  mongodb:
    image: mongo
    ports:
      - 27017:27017
    environment:
      - MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin
      - MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=password
  volumes:
    - mongo-data:/data/db     ## /data/db is the repo when mongo container store its data
                              ## that mean : attaching our volume "mongo-data" in the host to /data/db inside 
                              ## the container
                              ## ๐น mysql : /var/lib/mysql
                              ## ๐น postgres : /var/lib/postgres/data
  mongo-express:
    image: mongo-express
    ports:
      - 8082:8081
    environment:
      - ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINUSERNAME=admin
      - ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINPASSWORD=password
      - ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_SERVER=mongodb

volumes:              ## List all the volumes you are using in any of your containers
  mongo-data:         ## Name of the volume
    driver: local     ## Docker will create that PHYSICAL STORAGE ๐ข๏ธ in the LOCAL file system
